Here in the dark
Is no light at all,
No orientation,
No shadows fall.

Here in the dark
I reach out for you,
Sensing fear.
Have I lost you?

Is it you?
Is it you?

I see no way out.
I just hear your voice.
It seems so dead, too cold for you,
Too cold for you to be alive.

I hesitate
To trust your voice.
Sounds so unreal,
It sounds like if somebody forces you.

Is it you?
Is it you?

My hand stretches out,
Now I feel your hand.
It is motionless.
